			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">High lvl SKs<a name="54502"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 4:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Okay i've recently starting to hang out in the bazaar arena. I have a lot of fun because in a fair fight I almost never die, usually either win, the other person gives up, or we agree it's a stalemate. I have noticed gear doesn't particularly matter for me. Time equipped casters can still be ancient mezzed/drained. If they've got a pet I mez caster, let pet wack me with DS on until it's dead, and then go to draining the caster dry. Simply melee after that. Necros are tricky cause you have to keep them outta lich form. Priests, same concept. Always be sure to dispell a ton. Mez and drain them. Melee/ds after that. Rogues and monks are a joke. I just melee/ds and mez when I get low. You need some HP to do this with monks because if they have their mend AAs it will pop fairly often, and you have to let them wack you for a long time. Warriors same thing. Can be difficult cause some regen 100 hp per tick sitting so when you mez/regen they heal up too. Usually a stalemate in that case. Rangers? Just dispell their buffs and stay close enough that they eventually kill themselves on your DS. Pallys? Keep them drained and go in for short bits of melee. 
<br />

<br />
Now onto the actual topic of this post. The one class that I cannot seem to even stalemate unless their mana pool sucks are these d*mn shadownights. They chain life tap for 500 or so. You can't mez them in the beginning because they're in lich so you have to dispell it and while you're oding that, they're chain tapping. By the time you get them fully dispelled outta lich you're at 30%. Now you mez and drain them and regen. You move into melee and BAM....HT!!! Match over. 
<br />

<br />
It's to d*mn hard to time DA so that's it's on when they HT and if one manages to do so it would be pure luck. Any strats for dealing with SKs would be much appreciated.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
