				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: High lvl SKs<a name="54585"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 31 04 10:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Pumice Stones.
<br />

<br />
SK's are real monsters in PVP for bards, but the same holds true for them.  They hate bards.  The trick is that you gotta keep yourself healed up.  Having more room to work with then the arena in the bazaar helps a ton.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I find necro's are worse then SK's.  They tend to land them lifetaps more and theirs are bigger, and I usually ended up range dancing them.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
SK's usually tend to HT between 40 and 30%, but won't if they're whacking on you or whatever and your hp isn't moving...
<br />

<br />

<br />
My guild needs more necro's so I can have more experience :P.
<br />

<br />
Also, a warning - a lot of rangers will switch to 2Her or try out archery.  That strat will NOT work for you forever<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.  Personally, rangers, SK's, and wizards scare me<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
